grand.mean <- long %>%

              Median = median(y, na.rm=TRUE),
              SD = SD(y, na.rm=TRUE),
              obs = n() - sum(!is.na(y)))

Variable selection via buildmer¶

In [ ]:
max_mod <- buildmer((y ~ context + granularity + actors * (gender + education + diagnosis + marital + age + ethnicity + willingusetech + willingusecreditor + declaredbankruptcy + consideredbankruptcy + banked + impulsivelyspend + avoidmoneyanxious) + duration + (1|participant) + (1|item)), 
                    data=long, 
                    buildmerControl=list(REML=FALSE, include='(1|participant) + (1|item)',direction='backward', crit='BIC', ddf='lme4', args=list(control=lmerControl(optimizer='bobyqa'))))

Fitting ML and REML reference models

Fitting via lmer, with REML: y ~ context + granularity + actors * (gender + education + diagnosis + marital + age + ethnicity + willingusetech + willingusecreditor +
    declaredbankruptcy + consideredbankruptcy + banked + impulsivelyspend + avoidmoneyanxious) + duration + (1 | participant) + (1 | item)

fixed-effect model matrix is rank deficient so dropping 2 columns / coefficients

Fitting via lmer, with ML: y ~ context + granularity + actors * (gender + education + diagnosis + marital + age + ethnicity + willingusetech + willingusecreditor +
    declaredbankruptcy + consideredbankruptcy + banked + impulsivelyspend + avoidmoneyanxious) + duration + (1 | participant) + (1 | item)

fixed-effect model matrix is rank deficient so dropping 2 columns / coefficients

Create models¶

In [ ]:
model.0 <- lmer(y ~ actors + context + granularity + gender + education + diagnosis + marital + age + ethnicity + willingusetech + willingusecreditor + consideredbankruptcy + banked +
    impulsivelyspend + actors:gender + actors:marital + (1 | participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.1 <- lmer(y ~ actors * diagnosis + context + granularity + (1 | participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.2 <- lmer(y ~ actors * gender + granularity + context + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.3 <- lmer(y ~ actors * marital + context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.4 <- lmer(y ~ actors * age + context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.5 <- lmer(y ~ actors * willingusecreditor + context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.6 <- lmer(y ~ actors * willingusetech + context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.7 <- lmer(y ~ actors * granularity + context + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.8 <- lmer(y ~ actors * context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.9 <- lmer(y ~ actors * context * gender + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.10 <- lmer(y ~ actors * context * marital + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.11 <- lmer(y ~ actors * context * age + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.12 <- lmer(y ~ actors + context + granularity +(1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.13 <- lmer(y ~ actors * declaredbankruptcy + context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
model.14 <- lmer(y ~ actors * consideredbankruptcy + context + granularity + (1|participant), REML=FALSE, data=long)
